5:
...I'm so sorry, Hoshi. I should've
found you sooner.
8:
I wanted to apologize for what
happened that day...
11:
The truth is... I could have done
something. But instead... I...
29: I tried so hard to forget you!
50:
Ayumu, I'm afraid I... made a
mistake...
53:
Because of me... My mother and so
many others—
58: No! No, Hoshi! It... It wasn't your fault!
63:
I used the dragon to make a wish...
Have I been dreaming this whole
time?
73:
Oh... I see... I guess I made another
mistake...
76:
I'm sorry, Ayumu... It looks like I
messed up—
82: No! You have it all wrong! It's not you!
85: But it is... I did all of this...
91:
...I don't care. It doesn't matter
anymore...
102:
I said I don't care! So what if you
made a mistake? I'm fine with that!
105:
It doesn't matter how many times
you screwed up—hell, I don't care if
you destroyed the world!
109:
All I know is that I loved going to that
park and seeing you. When I was
there, I never felt alone.
113:
Hoshi... You're my friend! That's all
that matters... Nothing else!
121:
Wow, Ayumu... You really came all
this way to say that?
124:
Still, that just means I really did
mess things up...
127:
I should have just wished... to see
Mother one more time. That would
have been better...
132: Hoshi, Wait! We're not finished yet!
137: ...Kitty? I didn't know you were here...
151:
Thank you so much, Ayumu... For
coming to see me—for meeting me
in the park...
154: Goodbye. I'll always be... your friend...
172:
Stars above... You float alone in the
heavens, far beyond our reach.
174:
But to those people who likewise
drift in the darkness—those who are
lost, and desperately yearn for the
light—I say this.
177:
Have faith. Believe me when I say
that some day, the light WILL find
you—that someone WILL hear your
voice!
198:
Come ON! That was way, way, WAY
too close! Can you imagine if I'd
missed by even a LITTLE—
201:
Bah, no fair! I can't scold you when
you make a face like that.
206:
Nao was the one who found you
and pulled you out...
221:
I gave it some thought, you know. I
think we should still be partners in
crime.
230:
There's still a lot to do, after all. Let's
get through it together... and rope in
as many people as we can in the
process!
239:
Whoa, whoa, no need to cry or
anything! Think about your pretty
boy reputation—wouldn't want to
ruin that, right?
248:
You actually made it on time. Not
half bad.
253:
It's finally done, Alk. You saw your
mission through to the very end!
258:
Don't think you're off the hook for
that whole dyin' and comin' back
business. I've still got some choice
words for you later. But... I guess it
can wait.
262: What do you say we head on home?
